main event: A bright white object, about the size of a dime held at arm's length, was observed flying south in Cedar Key, Florida for two minutes.
interesting points: The object was first seen at an angle of about 20 degrees, then disappeared over the horizon.
The area of the sighting experiences a heavy amount of air traffic.
The report states that the sighting was possibly caused by an aircraft due to the duration of the sighting and the direction of the flight path.
The observation was made on April 3, 1956.
No photographs were taken of the object.
